WEBVTT

00:07.238 --> 00:09.291
That's the man
that has Nathan?

00:09.292 --> 00:11.676
No. A guy named Dmitri
has Nathan.

00:11.677 --> 00:13.795
That's a low-life
drug dealer.

00:13.796 --> 00:15.124
And?

00:15.125 --> 00:17.882
<i>And</i> I overheard
you and Quinn

00:17.883 --> 00:19.467
talking about
Clay's drug problem,

00:19.468 --> 00:22.757
so I decided to discourage
this dealer.

00:22.758 --> 00:24.759
What does this have to do
with Nathan?

00:24.760 --> 00:26.107
When I approached him,

00:26.108 --> 00:28.226
I overheard him
talking on the phone

00:28.227 --> 00:29.305
to a guy named Dmitri.

00:29.306 --> 00:31.724
How many Dmitris do you know
in Tree Hill?

00:33.765 --> 00:35.667
♪ Graceful ache

00:35.668 --> 00:36.938
[ door handle clicks ]

00:36.939 --> 00:39.940
Wait. I have waited long enough.
I want my husband back.

00:39.941 --> 00:41.206
What are you gonna do?

00:41.207 --> 00:42.407
You gonna walk up to him

00:42.408 --> 00:43.652
and ask him nicely
to tell you where Dmitri is?

00:43.653 --> 00:45.612
I don't plan
on asking him nicely.

00:45.613 --> 00:49.033
Look out that guy.
Take a good look.

00:49.034 --> 00:50.701
♪ Kindness

00:50.702 --> 00:53.913
You see anything there
that should make us concerned?

00:53.914 --> 00:55.831
Yeah.
He has a gun.

00:55.832 --> 00:58.623
He has a gun.
And we don't.

00:58.624 --> 01:00.891
So we have to be smart.

01:01.676 --> 01:04.227
Okay. All right.

01:06.399 --> 01:07.926
So, what's your plan?

01:09.653 --> 01:11.852
[ Police radio chatter ]

01:13.000 --> 01:19.074
Learn the unknown English words
of this movie at www.skeebdo.com

01:20.080 --> 01:22.166
I'm not the one you're supposed
to be arresting.

01:22.167 --> 01:24.582
That guy was beating
his son.

01:24.583 --> 01:25.736
And I stopped him.

01:32.217 --> 01:35.120
Son, we need to ask you
a few questions about tonight.

01:35.121 --> 01:37.790
Need you be honest
with me, okay?

01:37.791 --> 01:38.974
Did your father
hurt you earlier?

01:38.975 --> 01:40.960
Go ahead, sweetie.

01:40.961 --> 01:44.386
Tell the officer
the truth.

01:44.387 --> 01:46.938
Tell him
your father never...

01:46.939 --> 01:48.342
Laid a hand on you.

01:48.343 --> 01:52.305
Son, this is important.
Did your father hit you?

01:59.284 --> 02:00.896
No.

02:22.225 --> 02:23.335
Clay?

02:23.336 --> 02:25.710
You know
the traumatic event

02:25.711 --> 02:28.048
that I was hiding
from everyone,

02:28.049 --> 02:30.598
including myself?

02:30.599 --> 02:35.253
Well, we, uh,
we figured it out.

02:35.254 --> 02:38.105
And...

02:38.533 --> 02:39.893
He just had a birthday.

02:43.728 --> 02:45.483
We had a son, Quinn.

02:45.484 --> 02:48.610
Me and Sara.

02:48.611 --> 02:51.072
<i>I</i> have a son.

02:51.073 --> 02:55.076
H-how is that possible?

02:55.077 --> 02:59.110
Somehow I erased him
from my memory after her death.

02:59.111 --> 03:01.790
It's the reason
for my fugue state.

03:01.791 --> 03:03.959
I mean, a-are you sure?

03:03.960 --> 03:07.754
Yeah, I'm sure.

03:07.755 --> 03:09.086
Oh, God.

03:09.087 --> 03:11.589
It's been like waking up
from a dream. I just...

03:11.590 --> 03:15.143
The reality that I thought
I knew before made sense to me,

03:15.144 --> 03:17.861
but now I'm awake,
and I know what's true.

03:18.323 --> 03:20.264
I have a son.

03:20.265 --> 03:22.901
And, Quinn...

03:22.902 --> 03:23.938
It's Logan.

03:26.164 --> 03:28.943
Logan's <i>my</i> son.

03:31.836 --> 03:33.545
[ Baby fussing ]

03:33.546 --> 03:36.131
Just knowing that Xavier's
walking the same streets as us

03:36.132 --> 03:37.782
makes me feel sick.

03:37.783 --> 03:40.084
I'm not gonna be able
to sleep tonight.

03:40.085 --> 03:41.919
Maybe it wasn't him
at Karen's.

03:42.264 --> 03:43.788
Maybe it was just
in my head.

03:43.789 --> 03:45.473
He's putting us both
so on edge,

03:45.474 --> 03:47.086
maybe we're just jumping
at shadows.

03:47.087 --> 03:48.754
Do you really
believe that?

03:48.755 --> 03:50.756
I don't know.

03:50.757 --> 03:54.899
What I do know is that I'm here,
and our boys are here,

03:54.900 --> 03:56.803
and I'm not gonna let anything
happen to them.

03:56.804 --> 03:58.889
Or you. I promise.

04:04.659 --> 04:08.412
[ Mobile plays
"rock-a-bye baby" ]

04:16.036 --> 04:18.322
[ Door closes ]

04:18.322 --> 04:20.124
Sorry.
We're closed for the night.

04:20.125 --> 04:21.120
Man: I know.

04:24.996 --> 04:26.083
We're closed.

04:26.084 --> 04:27.334
So you said.

04:27.335 --> 04:29.003
Can I help you
with something?

04:29.004 --> 04:31.046
Yes, I think you can.

04:43.238 --> 04:44.273
Dude, wake up.

04:44.274 --> 04:45.560
W-what are you doing?

04:45.561 --> 04:47.438
Taking my dawg
out for a run.

04:47.439 --> 04:49.606
You got a dog?

04:49.607 --> 04:51.609
No, <i>you</i> my dawg, dawg.

04:51.610 --> 04:54.069
Did Millie put you
up to this?

04:54.070 --> 04:55.862
No.
<i>You</i> did, chubs.

04:55.863 --> 04:57.948
Am I really that bad?

04:57.949 --> 04:59.866
I'm thinking about changing
your name from mouth to chins.

04:59.867 --> 05:02.341
Now let's go!
Move, move, move!

05:02.342 --> 05:04.508
All right. I'm up.
I'm up.

05:13.969 --> 05:15.720
Morning.

05:17.773 --> 05:20.095
We had a crib with his name
above it.

05:20.096 --> 05:22.473
And a mobile of planes.

05:22.474 --> 05:24.229
I can see it
so clearly now.

05:24.230 --> 05:26.477
I-I just can't believe
I ever forgot about it.

05:26.478 --> 05:29.901
I just left him there.

05:29.902 --> 05:32.650
I had a son,
and I abandoned him.

05:32.651 --> 05:34.860
I mean,
trauma or no trauma,

05:34.861 --> 05:38.577
how the hell can someone erase
their own child for six years?

05:38.578 --> 05:41.158
I just left him there
and never went back.

05:41.159 --> 05:43.702
That doesn't mean
that you can't go back now.

05:43.703 --> 05:46.163
I don't know if I can.

05:46.164 --> 05:47.803
Of course you can.

05:47.804 --> 05:50.167
And I'm gonna go
with you.

05:51.673 --> 05:56.844
♪ And, ohhhh, I wander

05:59.047 --> 06:01.220
♪ 'cause when my shadow moves,
I shudder ♪

06:01.221 --> 06:02.763
Hey.
Here to fix your toilet.

06:02.764 --> 06:04.686
I... think you have
the wrong address.

06:04.687 --> 06:06.058
I didn't call
for a plumber.

06:06.059 --> 06:11.146
Hi. I hear you got a...
You got a backed-up toilet.

06:11.147 --> 06:13.858
No one called for a plumber.
Our toilet is fine.

06:13.859 --> 06:16.164
Um, no,
a Brooke Davis called me,

06:16.165 --> 06:18.283
and she said
to get here quick.

06:18.284 --> 06:19.835
"The toilet is backed up

06:19.836 --> 06:22.504
on account of the muffins
at Karen's café."

06:22.505 --> 06:23.839
I did not call
a plumber.

06:23.840 --> 06:25.907
There is <i>nothing</i> wrong
with our toilet.

06:25.908 --> 06:28.372
And there is certainly nothing
wrong with our muffins.

06:28.373 --> 06:30.712
Why would I volunteer
so much information?

06:30.713 --> 06:31.713
Brooke Davis?

06:31.714 --> 06:33.252
I'm here about
the broken crapper.

06:35.417 --> 06:36.463
Crap.

06:36.464 --> 06:39.554
Excuse me. [ Sighs ]

06:39.555 --> 06:42.223
Hi. It's <i>not</i> broken.

06:43.444 --> 06:47.891
♪ And I hope you understand

06:47.892 --> 06:50.198
♪ my strength lies...

06:50.199 --> 06:52.484
Where is that slut
you call a boss?

06:52.485 --> 06:54.898
Hi, Brooke.

06:58.834 --> 07:00.909
Welcome to Tree Hill café.

07:00.910 --> 07:04.532
How can I help you...
Neighbor?

07:04.533 --> 07:07.828
♪ And, ohhh, I live in fear

07:10.919 --> 07:12.921
Thanks for bailing me out.

07:12.922 --> 07:14.890
Not a problem.

07:14.891 --> 07:17.008
Couldn't leave you in the clink
too long,

07:17.009 --> 07:18.230
pretty little thing
like you.

07:18.231 --> 07:20.395
Just don't try
to skip bail.

07:20.396 --> 07:23.065
I got season two of
"dog the bounty hunter" at home.

07:23.066 --> 07:24.483
I picked up some pointers.

07:24.484 --> 07:25.683
Bro, I'll catch you.

07:27.802 --> 07:30.072
Don't worry.

07:30.073 --> 07:31.523
I'm not going anywhere.

07:31.524 --> 07:34.192
♪ You took my only one

07:34.193 --> 07:37.816
♪ when I only wanted love

07:37.817 --> 07:41.945
♪ when I only wanted love

07:41.946 --> 07:43.572
What the hell
are you doing?

07:43.573 --> 07:46.909
Um, running a decent café,
unlike you.

07:46.910 --> 07:49.077
How could you hire him?
He's a criminal.

07:49.078 --> 07:50.292
Who, Xavier?
[ Scoffs ]

07:50.293 --> 07:51.843
He needed a job.
We were hiring.

07:51.844 --> 07:54.162
Plus, I get a stipend
from the government

07:54.163 --> 07:55.960
for hiring a felon...
Win-win.

07:55.961 --> 08:00.118
He's a felon because
he kidnapped a child,

08:00.119 --> 08:02.507
robbed me,
and beat the hell out of me.

08:02.508 --> 08:05.907
Oh, my God.
I-I stand corrected.

08:05.908 --> 08:09.077
So really
it's a win-win-win,

08:09.078 --> 08:11.057
if you count the "beating
the hell out of you" part.

08:11.058 --> 08:12.647
Okay.

08:12.648 --> 08:15.617
You want to hang signs
and send roach-infested plants

08:15.618 --> 08:18.436
and clog my doorway with
the super Mario brothers,

08:18.437 --> 08:20.489
that's fine,
but he is dangerous.

08:20.490 --> 08:22.124
He murdered a kid!

08:22.125 --> 08:23.492
Correct me if I'm wrong,

08:23.493 --> 08:26.545
but, um, didn't you guys
have a convicted murderer

08:26.546 --> 08:29.075
flipping burgers for you
not too long ago?

08:29.076 --> 08:31.166
Tara,
please don't do this.

08:31.167 --> 08:33.705
I cannot have him working
so close to me.

08:33.706 --> 08:36.292
So if he stays, you go?

08:36.293 --> 08:38.376
[ Inhales sharply ]

08:38.378 --> 08:39.591
Perfect!

08:39.592 --> 08:42.255
So, really,
it's a win-win-win-win.

08:43.940 --> 08:45.258
Do be a stranger!

09:02.030 --> 09:03.448
Hey.

09:03.449 --> 09:06.070
[ Panting ]

09:06.502 --> 09:08.156
I'm out of shape.

09:08.157 --> 09:09.588
[ Chuckles ]

09:09.589 --> 09:12.290
Damn, dawg, you went
from De Niro in "Taxi Driver"

09:12.291 --> 09:14.125
to De Niro
in "Raging Bull."

09:14.126 --> 09:15.288
What the hell happened?

09:15.289 --> 09:19.080
Well, when you have
a job like mine,

09:19.081 --> 09:21.378
you have to eat out a lot.

09:21.379 --> 09:22.750
Yeah, well, when you have
a job like yours,

09:22.751 --> 09:23.755
you got to go
to the gym a lot.

09:23.756 --> 09:26.188
Well, you plan on going,
but something comes up,

09:26.189 --> 09:28.056
and you put it off
to the next day,

09:28.057 --> 09:29.757
so you wake up
a little heavier.

09:29.758 --> 09:31.860
You string enough
of these days together,

09:31.861 --> 09:33.348
and you just
wake up heavy.

09:35.230 --> 09:36.769
You know,
I heard somewhere

09:36.770 --> 09:39.401
that unhappy people
sometimes eat a lot

09:39.402 --> 09:41.440
to make theirself
feel better.

09:41.441 --> 09:43.191
And I'm saying this to you

09:43.192 --> 09:45.240
because you just don't seem like
the same happy-go-lucky mouth

09:45.241 --> 09:46.111
I used to know.

09:46.112 --> 09:47.112
Yeah?

09:47.113 --> 09:48.877
Yeah,
it's like if a sad mouth

09:48.878 --> 09:50.795
from a different dimension
came here

09:50.796 --> 09:53.298
and hunted down the happy mouth
and just ate him.

09:53.299 --> 09:56.418
[ Chuckles ]

09:56.419 --> 09:59.954
You know, I-I have felt a bit
of a weight lately,

09:59.955 --> 10:02.711
but I don't know
the cause of it.

10:02.712 --> 10:04.088
I think it's your ass.

10:04.089 --> 10:06.127
[ Both chuckle ]

10:06.128 --> 10:08.647
No, I have a great relationship
with Millie.

10:08.648 --> 10:11.466
We have a good life,
a good job.

10:11.467 --> 10:12.595
I'm pretty happy.

10:12.596 --> 10:15.807
Yeah, well,
I know something

10:17.449 --> 10:19.691
[ sighs ]

10:19.692 --> 10:20.854
50 push-ups.

10:20.855 --> 10:23.361
[ Chuckles ]

10:23.362 --> 10:24.733
Are you serious?

10:26.042 --> 10:28.148
[ Sighs ]

10:35.040 --> 10:37.342
[ Grunts ]
Would you settle for five?

10:37.343 --> 10:39.539
'Cause five would make me
unhappy, too.

10:39.540 --> 10:42.597
Wow.

10:42.598 --> 10:43.931
[ Clank ]

10:45.684 --> 10:48.503
That's what you meant
by being smart?

10:48.504 --> 10:50.639
He has a gun.
Now so do I.

10:50.640 --> 10:52.886
And this is
your master plan.

10:52.887 --> 10:55.644
This is not a disagreement
with someone

10:55.645 --> 10:57.057
at a pta meeting, Haley.

10:57.058 --> 10:58.934
These are
dangerous people.

10:58.935 --> 11:00.181
You want Nathan back,

11:00.182 --> 11:01.895
this might be what it takes
to get him back.

11:01.896 --> 11:03.897
You are gonna
get yourself killed.

11:03.898 --> 11:06.024
You have a better plan?

11:06.025 --> 11:09.194
Yeah, I do.

11:35.737 --> 11:37.313
How is it
that I have a son,

11:37.314 --> 11:39.698
and no one felt like
maybe they should share

11:39.699 --> 11:40.809
this information with me?

11:40.810 --> 11:42.144
When Sara was taken
from you...

11:42.145 --> 11:43.269
When Sara died.

11:43.270 --> 11:45.371
All right.

11:45.372 --> 11:46.705
When your wife died,

11:46.706 --> 11:49.408
in order to cope
with the sudden loss,

11:49.409 --> 11:51.243
your brain
removed the one thing

11:51.244 --> 11:54.740
that reminded you the most
of her... Logan.

11:56.507 --> 11:57.785
We tried, Clay.

11:57.786 --> 12:00.136
We tried telling you
during your early sessions,

12:00.137 --> 12:01.870
but you...
Or, rather, your brain...

12:01.871 --> 12:02.914
Just wouldn't hear it.

12:02.915 --> 12:05.542
When Logan was brought up,
you would shut down.

12:05.543 --> 12:07.461
All progress would be lost.

12:07.462 --> 12:09.379
So you just quit?
Clay...

12:09.380 --> 12:12.264
No, it's okay.

12:12.265 --> 12:13.341
<i>You</i> quit, Clay.

12:13.342 --> 12:15.677
You stopped coming
to your sessions,

12:15.678 --> 12:17.929
and you just...
You disappeared.

12:20.614 --> 12:22.643
So the state granted custody
to Sara's parents.

12:22.644 --> 12:25.144
But why has no one
tried to contact him since?

12:25.145 --> 12:28.447
I was the one who decided
we needed to wait for you

12:28.448 --> 12:29.816
to remember on your own.

12:32.126 --> 12:34.870
So if you want to be angry,
be angry with me.

12:34.871 --> 12:36.788
I don't want to be angry.

12:39.425 --> 12:41.495
I just need some guidance.

12:43.345 --> 12:47.433
I left him for <i>six</i> years.

12:47.434 --> 12:49.085
What do I do now?

12:49.086 --> 12:52.506
You should go talk
to your son.

12:52.507 --> 12:55.383
♪ I am only now

12:55.384 --> 12:59.596
♪ and a long way out

12:59.597 --> 13:01.897
♪ and don't you feel it... ♪

13:01.898 --> 13:02.849
You shouldn't be here.

13:02.850 --> 13:04.100
I need a minute.

13:13.417 --> 13:15.862
I may be going to jail
for a while...

13:15.863 --> 13:20.749
And I want to make sure
that Chuck is gonna be okay...

13:20.750 --> 13:25.037
That your husband is not
going to hurt him anymore.

13:25.038 --> 13:28.542
Not tomorrow, not next week,
not six months from now.

13:28.543 --> 13:33.729
[ Voice breaking ] When he gets
in one of his moods...

13:33.730 --> 13:35.898
I don't know what to do.

13:35.899 --> 13:37.766
I <i>try</i> to stop him.

13:37.767 --> 13:38.969
You need to try harder.

13:38.970 --> 13:41.187
And if that means getting him
out of your lives,

13:41.188 --> 13:42.722
then that's
what you need to do.

13:42.723 --> 13:45.107
Otherwise,
it's going to be Chuck

13:45.108 --> 13:47.060
who ends up
in the hospital.

13:47.061 --> 13:49.313
Please.

13:49.314 --> 13:51.522
Do it for Chuck.

13:56.952 --> 14:00.089
♪ Are last living feelings

14:00.090 --> 14:01.839
Chase!

14:03.633 --> 14:05.537
I'm sorry.

14:05.538 --> 14:07.496
Yeah.

14:07.497 --> 14:09.014
I know.

14:09.015 --> 14:13.044
♪ On account of what's to feel ♪

14:13.045 --> 14:15.836
[ engine turns over ]

14:16.972 --> 14:20.025
Well, first, he came to my café
and asked for a job.

14:20.026 --> 14:22.228
Then he came back
and ordered food.

14:22.229 --> 14:24.806
And now he's working
across the street from us.

14:24.807 --> 14:26.232
And he may have
been watching us

14:26.233 --> 14:27.559
through the café window
last night.

14:27.560 --> 14:30.102
What it sounds like to me
is we have an ex-con

14:30.103 --> 14:33.155
who was able to find employment
shortly after being paroled

14:33.156 --> 14:34.941
and who occasionally
gets hungry.

14:34.942 --> 14:36.776
I wish all my parolees
were this way.

14:36.777 --> 14:38.544
I'm sorry,
the way you say that

14:38.545 --> 14:40.113
makes us sound like
we're loony.

14:40.114 --> 14:41.863
Aren't there rules
against making contact

14:41.864 --> 14:43.033
with someone
you've attacked?

14:43.034 --> 14:44.200
Yes, there are.

14:44.201 --> 14:45.385
Well, there...
He broke the rules.

14:45.386 --> 14:46.835
But it's a small town.

14:46.836 --> 14:49.039
I mean,
paths <i>will</i> cross at times.

14:49.040 --> 14:51.307
He came to <i>my</i> place of work

14:51.308 --> 14:54.211
and asked <i>me</i> for a job
on purpose.

14:54.212 --> 14:55.877
Xavier informed me
of that incident

14:55.878 --> 14:57.263
shortly after it happened.

14:57.264 --> 14:59.064
He was not aware that you had
any connection with the café.

14:59.065 --> 15:00.216
He was just
looking for work.

15:00.217 --> 15:01.718
Come on!

15:01.719 --> 15:05.680
He came back after that
and... ate pie!

15:05.681 --> 15:07.740
If it will
make you feel better,

15:07.741 --> 15:10.693
I will call him this afternoon
and reiterate to him

15:10.694 --> 15:12.729
that he needs to stay away
from you.

15:14.663 --> 15:16.107
So that's it.

15:16.108 --> 15:17.333
Unfortunately, yes.

15:17.334 --> 15:19.084
I mean,
that's how the system works.

15:19.085 --> 15:20.169
Unless you have proof

15:20.170 --> 15:22.070
that Xavier's
doing something illegal,

15:22.071 --> 15:23.824
there's nothing more
that I can do.

15:23.825 --> 15:26.159
[ Brooke scoffs ]

15:26.160 --> 15:28.760
[ Hands clap legs ]

15:32.648 --> 15:34.633
Tell me this is
a shortcut.

15:34.634 --> 15:36.351
Nope.
It's the long way.

15:36.727 --> 15:39.520
But at least we get to stop by
and say hi to Jimmy.

15:40.889 --> 15:43.385
We were gonna host
"sportscenter" together.

15:43.386 --> 15:45.911
We even had
our own catchphrases.

15:45.912 --> 15:47.596
Mine was "wammo kablammo,"

15:47.597 --> 15:50.449
and his was, "now,
that's a spicy meatball."

15:50.450 --> 15:53.311
[ Scoffs ] Man, y'all was some dorks.
[ Chuckles ]

15:53.312 --> 15:55.937
There's not a day
that goes by

15:55.938 --> 15:58.390
where I don't think
about him.

15:58.391 --> 16:02.362
Somehow I still feel guilty
about how I lost touch with him.

16:02.363 --> 16:04.381
Yeah, mouth, but that wasn't
your fault, man.

16:04.547 --> 16:07.499
Yeah, I know.

16:07.500 --> 16:09.953
I miss you, Jimmy.

16:20.462 --> 16:21.730
He's over there,
you know.

16:21.731 --> 16:24.683
- Who?
- Xavier.

16:24.684 --> 16:26.719
The Xavier
who attacked you and...

16:26.720 --> 16:28.430
I didn't tell you?
No.

16:28.431 --> 16:30.656
He got hired
at the tree slut café,

16:30.657 --> 16:31.783
and it is wigging me out!

16:31.784 --> 16:34.310
What?
He can't do that, can he?

16:34.311 --> 16:36.245
Apparently.
I... you know what?

16:36.246 --> 16:37.813
I can't even talk
about it.

16:37.814 --> 16:39.690
You have some good news
about Nathan?

16:39.691 --> 16:41.834
No. Um [Chuckles] no.

16:41.835 --> 16:43.820
The police
are doing <i>nothing.</i>

16:43.821 --> 16:45.488
I'm sorry.

16:45.489 --> 16:46.781
So I went to Dan.

16:46.782 --> 16:47.907
Really?

16:47.908 --> 16:49.491
Yeah. At this point,

16:49.492 --> 16:52.378
I'm just willing to do whatever
it takes to get Nathan back.

16:52.379 --> 16:54.713
Dan has a lead,
and, um, that's why I'm here.

16:54.714 --> 16:56.632
I need your help
with something.

16:56.633 --> 16:58.335
Anything.

17:01.270 --> 17:02.671
♪ I guess ya never thought

17:02.672 --> 17:06.173
♪ that I'd be coming up
like a flame ♪

17:08.175 --> 17:09.778
♪ what's done is done, child ♪

17:09.779 --> 17:13.147
♪ and it's never gonna be
the same ♪

17:13.148 --> 17:15.143
♪ unh-unh

17:15.144 --> 17:18.820
♪ well, it's the last thing
