17:18.821 --> 17:20.455
♪ never gonna be the same

17:20.457 --> 17:21.958
♪ it's the last thing
I'll never do ♪

17:21.959 --> 17:24.159
Well?

17:24.160 --> 17:25.993
You just gonna sit there
and stare?

17:25.994 --> 17:27.656
Or you want to buy me
another one?

17:27.656 --> 17:31.300
♪ It's the last thing
I'll never do ♪

17:31.301 --> 17:33.537
♪ Now I'm falling away
from you ♪

17:38.726 --> 17:41.261
So, what do you think's
gonna happen?

17:41.262 --> 17:44.964
My best bet... I'm going to get
a dishonorable discharge,

17:44.965 --> 17:46.233
and once the dust settles,

17:46.234 --> 17:48.485
police will be there
to cart me off to prison.

17:48.486 --> 17:49.760
Good times.

17:49.761 --> 17:51.262
Dude, I'm sorry.

17:51.263 --> 17:54.325
I don't regret what I did
for a second.

17:54.326 --> 17:56.410
Guy had it coming...

17:56.411 --> 17:58.227
Beating on a kid.

17:58.228 --> 17:59.770
And Chuck lied, huh?

17:59.771 --> 18:01.315
He was just scared.

18:01.316 --> 18:02.690
He's been through a lot.

18:02.691 --> 18:05.819
Yeah, but still, you don't
deserve to go to jail.

18:10.841 --> 18:12.576
He should be in jail.

18:12.577 --> 18:14.535
I know I sound like
a broken record,

18:14.536 --> 18:16.296
but I don't think
I can handle

18:16.297 --> 18:18.248
seeing his psycho face
every day.

18:18.249 --> 18:20.250
Maybe you should stop
staring at him

18:20.251 --> 18:21.710
through the window,
then.

18:21.711 --> 18:23.044
What I mean is,

18:23.045 --> 18:25.889
it's probably best
if we both keep an eye on him,

18:25.890 --> 18:28.942
you know, like a two-person
neighborhood watch.

18:28.943 --> 18:30.644
I know what he's gonna do.

18:30.645 --> 18:34.114
He's gonna act all normal
and un-Norman bates-ish,

18:34.115 --> 18:36.867
and then once I drop
my guard... bam!

18:36.868 --> 18:38.351
That's when he strikes.

18:38.352 --> 18:40.120
Well, actually,
Norman bates

18:40.121 --> 18:42.039
acted relatively normal
in public.

18:42.040 --> 18:44.575
It was behind closed doors
that he was a psycho,

18:44.576 --> 18:46.484
so you can't really...

18:46.485 --> 18:49.613
You probably don't need a
film-history lesson right now.

18:49.614 --> 18:51.799
No.

18:51.800 --> 18:54.200
Haley's helping Dan
look for Nathan.

18:54.201 --> 18:55.718
Really?
That's an odd pairing.

18:55.719 --> 18:58.622
You know, the police
aren't doing anything,

18:58.623 --> 19:00.665
so she's looking
for him herself.

19:00.666 --> 19:03.293
[ Gasps ]
There he goes.

19:03.294 --> 19:05.212
Off to torture kittens

19:05.213 --> 19:09.799
or make dolls out of human hair
or whatever nutjobs do.

19:11.608 --> 19:12.969
Let's follow him.

19:12.970 --> 19:14.304
Are you serious?

19:14.305 --> 19:16.473
Brooke,
we have a family to protect.

19:16.474 --> 19:19.350
Having that creep on the streets
puts our boys at risk.

19:19.351 --> 19:22.103
Okay,
Haley has the right idea.

19:22.104 --> 19:24.415
I say we follow him
and see what he's up to.

19:24.416 --> 19:27.150
They need proof
that he's up to no good?

19:27.151 --> 19:28.067
Let's get proof.

19:28.068 --> 19:31.863
So the predator
becomes the prey.

19:34.258 --> 19:35.759
We have an emergency.

19:35.760 --> 19:37.127
Chase is in trouble.

19:37.128 --> 19:39.430
Come on.
What are we gonna do?

19:39.431 --> 19:41.799
[ Snapping fingers ]

19:41.800 --> 19:44.750
I know. This is big.
I'm speechless, too.

19:44.751 --> 19:46.335
He helped this little kid,
Chuck,

19:46.336 --> 19:47.504
and the kid lied
to the cops.

19:47.505 --> 19:48.421
You believe that?

19:48.422 --> 19:49.755
No.

19:49.756 --> 19:51.725
We could have
a benefit concert,

19:51.726 --> 19:53.110
get the media on our side.

19:53.111 --> 19:55.470
Or we could have a "save chase"
Twitter feed.

19:55.471 --> 19:57.388
Or you could just
go talk to the kid.

19:57.389 --> 19:58.515
Or that. Yeah.

19:58.516 --> 20:01.235
Okay. Okay.
These are good ideas.

20:01.236 --> 20:04.238
Let's keep brainstorming
in case we need a fall-back.

20:04.239 --> 20:05.563
Great work, team!

20:05.564 --> 20:07.657
Good enthusiasm!

20:10.494 --> 20:11.528
What's wrong?

20:11.529 --> 20:13.864
I don't know how
to do this.

20:13.865 --> 20:16.991
I mean, what am I
supposed to say to him?

20:16.992 --> 20:20.871
You've been talking to him
every day for the last week.

20:20.872 --> 20:24.424
Yeah, but that was before
I knew he was my son.

20:24.425 --> 20:26.143
He adores you.

20:26.144 --> 20:29.012
So just talk to him
like always,

20:29.013 --> 20:32.882
and at some point,
tell him you're his father.

20:34.885 --> 20:36.135
Clay...

20:36.136 --> 20:40.657
Just walk over and say,
"hi, Logan."

20:40.658 --> 20:43.184
Everything else
will come naturally.

21:00.294 --> 21:01.929
Hey, gambit.

21:01.930 --> 21:03.454
Gambit, huh?

21:03.455 --> 21:04.882
Yeah.

21:04.883 --> 21:06.958
I'm Wolverine,
and you're gambit.

21:06.959 --> 21:08.501
Nice.

21:08.502 --> 21:11.021
So, where have you been?

21:11.022 --> 21:13.131
Did you "lugue" again?

21:13.132 --> 21:14.558
[ Chuckles ]

21:14.559 --> 21:17.144
No, I-I didn't fugue.

21:17.145 --> 21:18.261
Something came up.

21:18.262 --> 21:20.430
And it was something
I had to think about,

21:20.431 --> 21:23.140
so I thought it'd be better
if I didn't do that here.

21:25.242 --> 21:26.602
So, you've been
eating well?

21:27.160 --> 21:27.905
Huh?

21:27.906 --> 21:31.566
You know, like,
lots of leafy greens...

21:31.567 --> 21:33.442
You're weird.

21:35.544 --> 21:38.048
Who's <i>this</i> guy?

21:38.049 --> 21:39.949
Oh, that's deadpool.

21:39.950 --> 21:41.576
Is he a good guy?

21:41.577 --> 21:43.253
Uh, it's hard to say.

21:43.254 --> 21:46.590
He's a hero for hire,
so sometimes he's good,

21:46.591 --> 21:48.165
but sometimes he's bad.

21:48.166 --> 21:50.293
The big thing
about this guy, though,

21:50.294 --> 21:53.764
is that he has healing powers
like Wolverine.

21:53.765 --> 21:55.131
And he's a bit
of a smartass.

21:57.982 --> 22:00.178
You just said a swear!

22:00.179 --> 22:03.173
Sorry.

22:03.174 --> 22:08.862
You know, swearing is bad,
so you just... just don't do it.

22:08.863 --> 22:10.605
And if you could,

22:10.606 --> 22:14.192
maybe don't mention it
to Dr. "a" on your next visit?

22:14.193 --> 22:15.943
Okay.

22:18.205 --> 22:20.340
Hey, Logan, has, uh,

22:20.341 --> 22:23.659
has the doctor ever talked
to you about your parents?

22:23.660 --> 22:24.911
Sometimes.

22:24.912 --> 22:27.371
Did he ever tell you
what happened to them?

22:27.372 --> 22:28.982
Yeah.

22:28.983 --> 22:31.876
My mom went to heaven
when I was a baby.

22:33.370 --> 22:34.712
How about your dad?

22:34.713 --> 22:37.941
He got really, really sad
when she died...

22:37.942 --> 22:40.510
So sad that he had
to go away.

22:40.511 --> 22:42.720
That sounds rough.

22:42.721 --> 22:45.082
But I don't care, though.

22:45.083 --> 22:49.436
Besides, spider-man lost
both of his parents, too.

22:49.437 --> 22:53.824
♪ ... In you the child
who lost its way ♪

22:53.825 --> 22:56.860
♪ to sail you from your

22:56.861 --> 23:01.747
♪ growing up sea of pain

23:04.084 --> 23:06.369
♪ and I swear...

23:06.370 --> 23:09.205
Hey, mini me.

23:09.206 --> 23:10.789
You doing okay?

23:12.843 --> 23:15.419
Chase is going to jail,
and it's all my fault.

23:15.420 --> 23:19.923
I should have told the cops
the truth.

23:19.924 --> 23:21.268
I should have told them

23:21.269 --> 23:23.761
that he was just trying to get
my dad to stop hitting me.

23:25.945 --> 23:27.974
Is he mad at me?

23:27.975 --> 23:30.277
No.

23:30.278 --> 23:31.611
He understands.

23:31.612 --> 23:33.896
He just wants to make sure
<i>you're</i> gonna be okay.

23:36.366 --> 23:38.150
Are you mad at me?

23:38.151 --> 23:40.170
No.

23:40.171 --> 23:41.922
No, I'm not mad at you.

23:41.923 --> 23:44.925
No, Chris Keller
knows how hard it is

23:44.926 --> 23:46.617
to do the right thing.

23:46.618 --> 23:50.347
Funny thing is, is you keep
trying to be like me...

23:50.348 --> 23:52.182
Which is understandable.

23:52.183 --> 23:53.499
I'm pretty kick-ass.

23:53.500 --> 23:58.254
But you should be trying
to be like chase.

23:58.255 --> 24:00.023
I mean,
he did the right thing

24:00.024 --> 24:02.592
even though he was afraid
of what could happen.

24:02.593 --> 24:05.193
♪ ... Falls on you

24:11.602 --> 24:14.787
[ novosti's "at the bonfire"
plays ]

24:17.240 --> 24:19.233
Brooke: Maybe this isn't
the best idea.

24:19.234 --> 24:21.778
What, stalking the guy
who's been stalking us?

24:21.779 --> 24:23.964
No, it's not that.
This could take forever.

24:23.965 --> 24:25.615
What are we
supposed to do,

24:25.616 --> 24:27.884
follow him all day
till he commits a crime?

24:27.885 --> 24:32.580
♪ And we'll get
our story right ♪

24:36.292 --> 24:43.132
♪ we've been divided,
broke in the morning light ♪

24:43.133 --> 24:44.985
well, that didn't
take very long.

24:44.986 --> 24:47.428
♪ Hey, hey

24:48.862 --> 24:51.858
Hello, 911?
I'd like to report a break-in.

24:51.859 --> 24:54.744
♪ ... To our savior

24:57.531 --> 24:59.148
So then I broke his arm.

24:59.617 --> 25:01.317
And then I told him

25:01.318 --> 25:04.921
if he didn't give me
the money he owed me,

25:04.922 --> 25:09.126
then I would continue to break
every bone in his body...

25:09.127 --> 25:11.327
In alphabetical order.

25:11.328 --> 25:14.747
Which works,
because I started with his arm.

25:14.748 --> 25:17.601
[ Chuckles ]
Oh, right.

25:17.602 --> 25:19.019
[ Chuckles ]

25:19.020 --> 25:20.637
That's funny.

25:20.638 --> 25:22.630
You're funny.

25:22.631 --> 25:25.216
You're a real,
um, tough guy, huh?

25:25.217 --> 25:26.943
I like that in a man.

25:26.944 --> 25:29.279
You know what I like
in a woman?

25:29.280 --> 25:30.781
Hmm?

25:30.782 --> 25:31.889
Me.

25:31.890 --> 25:32.899
Oh.

25:32.900 --> 25:35.685
Do your shot.

25:35.686 --> 25:36.870
[ Chuckles ]

25:36.871 --> 25:38.455
♪ the glory goes to you

25:38.456 --> 25:41.657
♪ I don't suppose that you ♪

25:44.878 --> 25:46.913
[ clears throat ]

25:46.914 --> 25:49.365
This has been real fun.

25:49.366 --> 25:52.335
I think I'm gonna need
something else, though.

25:52.336 --> 25:55.672
Something that's gonna,
you know, get me in the mood,

25:55.673 --> 25:57.581
if you know
what I'm saying.

25:57.582 --> 26:01.627
You want to party with me
or my product?

26:01.628 --> 26:04.714
Let's make it a threesome.

26:04.715 --> 26:06.507
That works for me, girl.

26:06.508 --> 26:08.675
Come on.

26:19.663 --> 26:22.732
Damn, girl.
I can't wait to hit that.

26:22.733 --> 26:24.500
That's just
what I was thinking.

26:33.677 --> 26:37.180
♪ LA-da-da-da

26:37.181 --> 26:39.715
♪ LA-da-da-da

26:43.717 --> 26:45.885
[ police radio chatter ]

26:48.055 --> 26:49.740
What the hell
is taking so long?

26:49.741 --> 26:51.609
He should be some prisoner's
bitch by now.

26:51.610 --> 26:53.661
Are you the ones that reported
the break-in?

26:53.662 --> 26:55.613
Yes, sir. Do you need
a statement or something?

26:55.614 --> 26:57.642
When you arrest him,
can I slap the cuffs on him?

26:57.643 --> 26:58.726
We're not arresting him.

26:58.727 --> 26:59.727
What do you mean?
What?

26:59.728 --> 27:00.936
He didn't break in
the house.

27:00.937 --> 27:03.037
We just saw him
climb in the window.

27:03.038 --> 27:05.006
The house belongs
to a friend of his.

27:05.007 --> 27:07.067
He's staying there,
and he forgot his key.

27:07.068 --> 27:08.609
It all checks out.

27:08.610 --> 27:10.028
Oh.

27:10.029 --> 27:13.657
♪ I know there'll be days
we'll say our sorries ♪

27:16.184 --> 27:22.249
♪ there'll be times
we won't accept apologies ♪

27:22.250 --> 27:27.395
♪ and endless nights
in bed together ♪

27:27.396 --> 27:31.232
♪ facing opposite directions

27:31.233 --> 27:35.602
♪ it's not easy
when you're stubborn ♪

27:36.737 --> 27:41.774
♪ even worse, so is your lover

27:44.078 --> 27:47.048
♪ I have found

27:47.049 --> 27:49.584
♪ I found in you

27:49.585 --> 27:50.819
♪ I found a friend

27:50.820 --> 27:53.337
So, you found him
by the pool,

27:53.338 --> 27:55.806
on the beach,
on the playground.

27:55.807 --> 27:58.952
All the places
you would take your child.

27:58.953 --> 28:00.761
And now that he knows
about Logan,

28:00.762 --> 28:02.831
the fugue state no longer
has a purpose.

28:02.832 --> 28:04.416
So he's cured?

28:04.417 --> 28:05.733
For the most part.

28:05.734 --> 28:07.468
He'll need to go
to therapy

28:07.469 --> 28:10.438
in order to, uh, work through
some of the issues

28:10.439 --> 28:11.757
he needs to address.

28:11.758 --> 28:14.509
It'll take time.

28:14.510 --> 28:17.013
He's on his way.

28:17.014 --> 28:18.847
We'll get through it.

28:18.848 --> 28:23.269
He told me he loves you,
by the way.

28:23.270 --> 28:25.670
That totally breaks
patient-doctor confidentiality,

28:25.671 --> 28:27.505
but...

28:27.506 --> 28:31.359
Then, you knew it already,
so, what the hell?

28:31.360 --> 28:33.043
Thank you.

28:40.051 --> 28:41.702
Man: Airman Adams,
to attack a civilian

28:41.703 --> 28:43.588
is an act that casts shame
and embarrassment

28:43.589 --> 28:44.999
on your fellow airmen.

28:45.000 --> 28:49.226
Your actions were unbecoming
of a member of the air force.

28:52.346 --> 28:54.348
It seems we have
a character witness here

28:54.349 --> 28:56.052
to speak on your behalf.

29:02.281 --> 29:03.976
At ease, young man.

29:06.578 --> 29:10.498
I know that you guys want to
kick chase out of the air force

29:10.499 --> 29:13.633
because you think
he did something wrong.

29:14.585 --> 29:15.779
But he didn't.

29:18.090 --> 29:20.207
I did.

29:20.208 --> 29:22.411
'Cause I didn't tell
the truth.

29:27.598 --> 29:29.066
My dad hits me.

29:29.067 --> 29:33.437
He hits me even when I haven't
done anything wrong.

29:33.438 --> 29:37.260
Chase found out,
and he stopped him.

29:39.319 --> 29:40.361
[ Sighs ]

29:40.362 --> 29:42.496
I know I shouldn't have
lied about it.

29:42.497 --> 29:43.864
But I did.

29:43.865 --> 29:44.850
And I'm sorry.

29:46.576 --> 29:49.105
So it's my fault.

29:49.106 --> 29:51.565
Chase was protecting me.

29:51.566 --> 29:54.792
Isn't that
what you taught him to do?

29:54.793 --> 29:56.460
He's really nice to me

29:56.461 --> 29:59.597
and helps me
with all kinds of stuff.

29:59.598 --> 30:01.992
All he ever wanted to do
was fly.

30:02.517 --> 30:05.662
Please don't take that away
from him.

30:16.022 --> 30:17.031
Hey, Jimmy.

30:17.032 --> 30:19.116
I know
what you're thinking.

30:19.117 --> 30:22.269
"I haven't heard
from my pal mouth in ages,

30:22.270 --> 30:25.265
and what's this...
Two visits in one day?"

30:25.266 --> 30:27.825
Well, I've been working
on a sports blog,

30:27.826 --> 30:32.111
and... I thought maybe you could
help me with it.

30:41.172 --> 30:42.306
[ Grunting ]

30:42.307 --> 30:43.457
What the hell <i>is</i> this?

30:43.458 --> 30:45.809
This is me finding out
where my husband is.

30:46.260 --> 30:48.145
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

30:48.146 --> 30:51.015
And if I did, I'd say that
he had his teeth pulled out

30:51.016 --> 30:52.918
and his fingers
cut off by now.

30:52.919 --> 30:54.485
I want to know where...
Haley!

30:54.486 --> 30:56.963
He can't tell us anything
if you beat him to death.

30:56.964 --> 30:59.174
Whoo-whee.
That's a crazy bitch.

30:59.175 --> 31:00.885
♪ Your dark eyes

31:00.886 --> 31:04.412
♪ deep as a well

31:04.413 --> 31:06.146
what did you do to him?!

31:06.147 --> 31:07.448
Get her off of me!
No!

31:07.449 --> 31:09.867
[ Grunts ]
Get this bitch off of me!

31:09.868 --> 31:11.318
Okay.

31:11.319 --> 31:13.480
Your husband's dead,
you stupid whore.

31:13.872 --> 31:17.090
[ Laughs ]
Shut up!

31:18.659 --> 31:22.615
♪ ... With me just as well

31:22.616 --> 31:24.533
You need to go now.

31:24.534 --> 31:27.077
I'm not going anywhere until
I find out where Nathan is.

31:27.078 --> 31:28.662
[ Muffled speaking ]

31:29.104 --> 31:30.872
♪ everything's gone ♪

31:30.873 --> 31:33.251
I'm gonna need to do some things
you shouldn't see.

31:33.252 --> 31:34.793
I can handle it.

31:34.794 --> 31:37.478
Haley... he's going to talk,
and we're going to find Nathan.

31:37.479 --> 31:38.696
Trust me.

31:38.697 --> 31:40.340
But I can't have you here
when I do this.

31:40.341 --> 31:43.302
So go home.

31:43.303 --> 31:46.203
I'll call you.

31:46.204 --> 31:49.656
Be sure to give Deb back
her clothes.

31:52.025 --> 31:53.729
Bring Nathan home.

31:53.730 --> 31:57.415
I don't care
<i>what</i> it takes.

31:57.416 --> 31:59.068
Bring him home.

32:09.176 --> 32:11.330
[ Coughs ]

32:16.183 --> 32:18.352
Well, well, well.

32:18.353 --> 32:20.422
Alone at last.

32:40.000 --> 32:41.241
Alone at last.

32:41.242 --> 32:42.528
[ Keys clatter ]

32:42.529 --> 32:44.237
[ Panting ]

32:48.591 --> 32:50.160
Look...

32:50.161 --> 32:53.413
Shh!

32:53.414 --> 32:55.022
You've already done
enough talking today

32:55.023 --> 32:56.774
with that pretty little mouth
of yours.

32:56.775 --> 32:57.793
How 'bout you just listen?

32:59.769 --> 33:02.413
I know I hurt you
in the past,

33:02.414 --> 33:03.948
but that's the past.

33:03.949 --> 33:06.767
I served my time
for what I did,

33:06.768 --> 33:10.056
and now I'm just trying
to get on with my life.

33:10.057 --> 33:12.606
But you keep pushing me.

33:12.607 --> 33:14.810
You need to stop.

33:14.811 --> 33:16.854
'Cause you should know...

33:18.779 --> 33:22.735
... that I can get to you
whenever I want.

33:25.503 --> 33:27.489
So don't give me
a reason to.

33:31.892 --> 33:33.370
Dropped these.

33:39.683 --> 33:41.985
Have a nice night.

33:59.907 --> 34:03.358
Hmm.
Told you we'd fix it.

34:03.359 --> 34:06.848
I know.
I can't wait to crash it again.

34:06.849 --> 34:08.947
[ Chuckles ]

34:08.947 --> 34:10.549
Hey, about
what you said earlier...

34:10.550 --> 34:14.245
Do you really not care what
happened to your mom and dad?

34:14.246 --> 34:15.286
I don't know.

34:15.288 --> 34:16.996
Do you ever think
about your dad?

34:16.998 --> 34:20.695
I guess <i>sometimes</i> I think
about what he might be like.

34:20.696 --> 34:22.263
And what do you think?

34:22.264 --> 34:23.670
Promise you won't laugh?

34:23.670 --> 34:25.505
Promise.

34:25.507 --> 34:29.085
Well, I like to think
that he's a superhero,

34:29.087 --> 34:32.356
like in "X-Men,"
out fighting bad guys.

34:32.357 --> 34:34.158
Or he's a secret agent,

34:34.159 --> 34:38.060
and he's got a flying car
and a jet pack and stuff.

34:38.061 --> 34:40.231
[ Sighs ]

34:40.232 --> 34:42.783
Would you settle
for a regular agent...

34:42.784 --> 34:43.940
The non-secret kind?

34:43.940 --> 34:45.686
I guess.

34:45.687 --> 34:49.340
I just hope that maybe one day
he'll come home.

34:49.341 --> 34:52.824
Then maybe neither of us
will be sad anymore.

34:54.962 --> 34:57.329
Logan,
you know my problem.

34:57.330 --> 35:00.234
You know, I wander around
like I'm someone else.

35:00.235 --> 35:01.458
Well...

35:01.459 --> 35:06.463
Dr. "a" was able to help me
figure out why I was doing it.

35:06.464 --> 35:08.257
And how come?

35:08.258 --> 35:13.080
Well, a few years ago,
something bad happened.

35:13.081 --> 35:17.835
I lost someone that I loved
very, very much...

35:17.836 --> 35:19.537
My wife.

35:19.538 --> 35:21.520
When it happened,

35:21.521 --> 35:25.259
my brain just made me
forget things

35:25.260 --> 35:27.878
that reminded me of her
so I'd be less sad.

35:27.879 --> 35:31.654
But... now my brain
wants me to remember.

35:33.381 --> 35:38.829
The person that I lost, Logan,
was your mom.

35:40.888 --> 35:43.250
I'm your father.

35:43.251 --> 35:46.503
You're... you're my son.

35:46.504 --> 35:52.403
I-I know I don't have
a flying car or anything,

35:52.404 --> 35:57.742
but... I'd really like
to be a part of your life.

35:57.743 --> 36:00.726
And I'd really like it
if you'd be a part of mine.

36:00.727 --> 36:03.580
Would you like that?

36:07.218 --> 36:08.608
Logan?

36:08.609 --> 36:10.485
No.

36:26.988 --> 36:27.961
I'm out.

36:27.962 --> 36:30.224
What?!

36:30.225 --> 36:31.859
That is such
a load of crap!

36:31.860 --> 36:33.577
You know,
Chris Keller thinks

36:33.578 --> 36:36.030
that those jackasses
weakened our nation today!

36:36.031 --> 36:38.064
Could have been
a lot worse.

36:38.529 --> 36:40.701
I was only given
a general discharge,

36:40.702 --> 36:42.059
not a dishonorable one.

36:42.060 --> 36:44.019
So I got that
going for me.

36:44.020 --> 36:46.540
Now I just have to hope
they don't send me to prison

36:46.541 --> 36:47.874
for the next three years.

36:48.959 --> 36:49.942
They're not going to.

36:49.943 --> 36:51.610
Right, mom?

36:51.611 --> 36:54.029
No. They're not.

36:54.030 --> 36:55.573
Wade's been arrested.

36:55.574 --> 36:57.718
I reported him
to the police

36:57.719 --> 37:00.536
and told them that you acted
in defense of Chuck.

37:02.220 --> 37:04.498
Is the air force
still gonna let you fly planes?

37:04.499 --> 37:08.418
No, Chuck.

37:08.419 --> 37:10.431
At least not for them.

37:10.432 --> 37:13.340
So what I said
didn't mean anything.

37:13.341 --> 37:15.286
Hey...

37:15.287 --> 37:16.802
What you said
meant everything.

37:16.803 --> 37:18.803
[ Robin foster's "forgiveness"
plays ]

37:23.782 --> 37:26.914
♪ I remember...

37:26.915 --> 37:28.229
You, wake up.

37:28.230 --> 37:30.941
Baby, please,
I am not from havana.

37:30.942 --> 37:32.085
Skills.

37:33.838 --> 37:34.903
What up?

37:34.904 --> 37:36.280
You want to go
to the gym?

37:38.392 --> 37:40.241
For sure,
my chubby buddy.

37:40.242 --> 37:44.454
What the hell
do you dream about?

37:44.455 --> 37:48.768
♪ I had to forget...
What?

37:50.309 --> 37:51.355
Haley: He did <i>what?</i>

37:51.356 --> 37:52.606
Xavier scared the hell
out of me

37:52.607 --> 37:54.089
and then told me
I need to leave him alone.

37:54.090 --> 37:56.243
Did he tell you
or threaten you?

37:56.244 --> 37:57.301
Both.

37:57.302 --> 37:58.479
I don't know.

37:58.480 --> 38:00.220
It felt pretty threatening
and creepy.

38:00.221 --> 38:03.014
Brooke,
you need to call the police.

38:03.015 --> 38:05.558
They're not gonna do anything
except for maybe set him off.

38:05.559 --> 38:07.478
Well,
what does Julian think?

38:07.479 --> 38:09.187
I didn't tell him.

38:09.188 --> 38:10.730
Brooke!

38:10.731 --> 38:13.043
Haley, if I tell Julian,
he's gonna go after Xavier

38:13.044 --> 38:15.212
and then either murder him
or get murdered by him,

38:15.213 --> 38:17.498
and either way, my boys grow up
without a father.

38:17.499 --> 38:20.101
What are you gonna do?

38:20.102 --> 38:23.137
I don't know.

38:23.138 --> 38:24.605
Let's talk
about something else.

38:24.606 --> 38:25.996
Did everything go okay
with you?

38:25.997 --> 38:27.391
Um, yeah.

38:27.392 --> 38:30.060
Considering
the circumstances...

38:30.061 --> 38:31.362
Everything went great.

38:31.363 --> 38:32.696
Um...

38:32.697 --> 38:35.672
It's just kind of
up to Dan now, I guess.

38:35.673 --> 38:39.092
What happened
to our world?

38:39.093 --> 38:44.024
♪ I carry this rock

38:44.025 --> 38:46.360
♪ this old dead weight

38:46.361 --> 38:47.795
What are you doing awake?

38:47.796 --> 38:50.881
- ♪ Like a noose around my throat... ♪
- Huh?

38:50.882 --> 38:53.667
Hey. Hey.

38:53.668 --> 38:55.553
It's okay.

38:55.554 --> 38:58.556
Oh, it's okay.
Mommy's here.

38:58.557 --> 38:59.905
And she always will be.

38:59.906 --> 39:04.228
♪ This will be my lonely end

39:04.229 --> 39:05.646
You're dead.

39:05.647 --> 39:07.214
You know that?

39:07.215 --> 39:09.733
Dead!

39:09.734 --> 39:13.053
There's something
you should know about me.

39:13.054 --> 39:16.240
I don't do well
with threats.

39:16.241 --> 39:21.395
You see, I'm gonna find my son
whether you talk or not.

39:21.396 --> 39:24.512
They only thing is...

39:24.513 --> 39:27.168
Will you still be breathing
when I do?

39:27.169 --> 39:29.587
♪ ... To pray forgiveness

39:29.588 --> 39:34.758
♪ but I won't swallow ♪

39:34.759 --> 39:38.462
♪ what they feed us

39:38.463 --> 39:40.381
Now, I'm gonna ask you
a few questions,

39:40.382 --> 39:42.633
and you feel free to scream out
the answers.

39:42.634 --> 39:44.768
See...

39:44.769 --> 39:47.661
That's the good news about
having your own sound stage.

39:50.471 --> 39:52.526
No one can
hear you scream.

39:52.527 --> 39:55.001
♪ No more

39:55.002 --> 39:57.815
♪ no more

39:57.816 --> 40:00.234
[ screams ]

40:00.235 --> 40:05.387
♪ no more

40:05.388 --> 40:10.777
♪ no more

40:10.778 --> 40:15.332
♪ no more

40:15.333 --> 40:20.387
♪ no more

40:20.388 --> 40:25.156
♪ no more

40:25.157 --> 40:30.598
♪ no more

40:30.599 --> 40:34.768
♪ no more...

